.Dd @DATE@
.Dt wilddns-conf 8
.Os @VERSION@
.Sh NAME
.Nm wilddns-conf
.Nd sets up an domain-name-listing DNS service (IPv4 network connection)
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm wilddns-conf
.Ar acct
.Ar logacct
.Ar D
.Ar ip
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm wilddns-conf
creates a service directory
.Ar D
that runs
.Xr wilddns 8 .
The name
.Ar D
must start with a slash and must not contain any special characters.
Normally
.Ar D
is
.Pa /etc/wilddns .
.Pp
You can run the service under
.Xr svscan 8
by creating a symbolic link in the
.Xr svscan 8
directory:
.Pp
.Dl "ln -s" Ar D Ns Pa /service
.Pp
The service will start within five seconds, and will be restarted upon reboot.
You can use
.Xr svctl 8
to control the service.
.Pp
.Nm wilddns-conf
arranges for
.Xr wilddns 8
to chroot to
.Ar D Ns Pa /root
and to run under the uid and gid of
.Ar acct .
The name
.Ar acct
must not contain any special characters.
.Pp
.Nm wilddns-conf
creates
.Ar D Ns Pa /root/Makefile
to run
.Xr wilddns-data 8
upon request.
.Pp
.Nm wilddns-conf
arranges for
.Xr wilddns 8
to listen for UDP packets on port 53 of
.Ar ip ,
and to send outgoing packets from
.Ar ip .
.Pp
.Nm wilddns-conf
creates an automatically rotated log directory in
.Ar D Ns Pa /log/main .
The logs are owned by
.Ar logacct .
The corresponding
.Xr multilog 8
processes run under the uid and gid of
.Ar logacct .
The name
.Ar logacct
must not contain any special characters.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr wilddns 8 ,
.Xr wilddns6 8 ,
.Xr wilddns-data 8
.Xr svscan 8 ,
.Xr svctl 8 ,
.Xr multilog 8 ,
.Xr axfrdns-conf 8 ,
.Xr dnscache-conf 8 ,
.Xr tinydns-conf 8 ,
.Xr walldns-conf 8
.Pp
